                            jump to other results
                        </a></div></div><ol class="sense_single" htag="ol"><li class="sense" htag="li" hclass="sense" id="adams_sng_1"><span class="sensetop" htag="span" hclass="sensetop"><span class="def" hclass="def" htag="span">(1902-85) a US photographer who took black and white photographs of the US South-West. One of his best-known books was <span class="ebi">Taos Pueblo</span> (1930). He helped to create the department of photography at the <a class="Ref" href="https://www.oxfordlearnersdictionaries.com/definition/english/the-museum-of-modern-art#the_museum_of_modern_art_topg_1" title="Museum of Modern Art definition"><span class="ndv">Museum of Modern Art</span></a> in New York in 1940, and was Director of the Sierra Club, an organization to protect nature, for 37 years.</span></span>    <div id="ring-links-box">
